76. minor, subject. Cf. Od. I. 12. 57.-vindicta: in the process of manumission per vindictam, a *for- mal claimant asserted a right to the slave by striking him with a rod3 the master abandoned his claim, and the praetor then declared him free. In the case of a slave to passion, such a process would be tried in vain; hence how much more a slave is he.

78. super: cf. Ep. 11. 2. 33.

79. vicarius: a slave bought by another out of his peculium to take his place.

80. tibi, etc.: i.e. I am only a vicarius or conservus, and yet you pretend to be my master.

81. alii, i.e. to your passions.
